accessibility.text: Front Art Space, New York City’s smallest art gallery, sought a provocative and interactive installation. Pith designed a monthlong pop-up, making use of specially commissioned porcelain ceramics and corresponding bent-metal furniture. During the residency, Jonah cooked and dined with unsuspecting pedestrians. Sound artists occasionally joined in to provide a sonic backdrop. At the close of the installation, longer dinners were auctioned off whereby guests would take home the ceramics used.

Octopus with paprika, peppercorn, pistachio-truffle tapenade. Chrysanthemum and rosehip tea. Rhubarb and clove compote, hopped whipped cream, micro shiso. Pumpernickel, goat’s kefir, oregano, fava bean.
